nce(shadowBranch)\\n    → extractSessionData()  [parses metadata on shadow branch]\\n```\\n\\n### Per-Session Costs in filterSessionsWithNewContent\\n\\nFor **each session** (up to N), the code calls:\\n\\n1. **`repo.Reference(shadowBranch, true)` - ~4-5ms**\\n   - File: `manual_commit_hooks.go:1131`\\n   - This performs a full ref lookup from the git object database\\n   - With 200 branches + packed-refs, this is NOT a simple hash table lookup\\n   - `go-git` iterates through references to find the branch\\n   - Called **once per session** to check if shadow branch exists\\n\\n2. **`commit.Tree()` - ~0.5-1ms**\\n   - Resolves git tree object from commit\\n   - Small but adds up across N sessions\\n\\n3. **`tree.File(metadataDir + \\\"/\\\" + transcriptFileName)` - ~1-2ms**\\n   - Traverses the tree to find the transcript file\\n   - For shadow branches with deep metadata structure\\n\\n4. **`countTranscriptItems(content)` - ~2-3ms for 200+ JSONL lines**\\n   - Parses entire transcript JSONL to count entries\\n   - File: `manual_commit_condensation.go:549`\\n   - Done for each session to check `hasTranscriptGrowth`\\n\\n5. **`stagedFilesOverlapWithContent()` (conditional) - ~2-5ms if called**\\n   - Compares staged files against session's FilesTouched\\n   - File: `content_overlap.go:185`\\n   - Only called if staged files exist AND session has files\\n\\n**Total per-session in filterSessionsWithNewContent: ~10-16ms per session**\\n\\n### Additional Costs\\n\\n6. **`listAllSessionStates()` - O(N) overhead**\\n   - File: `manual_commit_session.go:60-102`\\n   - `store.List(ctx)` = O(N) readdir + N × Load\\n   - Each `Load()` parses JSON, normalizes, checks staleness\\n   - Called **once at PrepareCommitMsg start**, but the ref checks inside happen again\\n   - Extra cost: ~3-5ms per session from Load\\n\\n7. **`getLastPrompt()` - ~4-8ms for non-empty sessions**\\n   - File: `manual_commit_hooks.go:1841-1861`\\n   - Called once for first session with content\\n   - `r